    title: "Evaluation tells you if an agent can work. Observability tells you if it is.",
    dek: "JetBrains on the distinction that defines production AI monitoring: evaluation is offline and benchmark-based. Observability is live and continuous. Most teams have one. Almost none have both. And having only one means you're blind in the other direction.",
    author: "Genesis",
    date: "May 25, 2026",
    read: 3,
